description: Enjoying a nice glass of bubbly

New and as far as I know, the only “pocket park” or mini park in Memphis. It now lives where a dilapidated Burger King restaurant used to be. Designed by the PARC Foundation in New York.

I love this space. There’s an art gallery below and jasmine vines looping through the fencing that borders the park. It’s a must-see if you ever visit Memphis.
